description:
NEW ONGOING SERIES! The end of the world is here... The horror continues as a zombified Jughead goes on a relentless hunt for brains in this shocking new series by Harvey Award-winning comic/screenwriter Roberto Aguirre-Sacasa (Stephen King's Carrie, Archie meets Glee) and Eisner-winning artist Francesco Francavilla (Batman, Black Beetle). When he performs a despicable and frightening act in front of everyone at the Halloween dance, tensions start to rise and fears begin to mount -- who will be next to join Jughead in the Afterlife? And what about those who are already infected? Be warned, kiddies, this one's not for the faint of heart!

description: We find our group recovering from a devastating wyrm attack when things go from worse to dreadful as a particular black dragon returns home. Also, in this issue Dominic, Silverfawn and Letha discover a forgotten race of ancient beings who are in a quandary...the ruling council want to keep things as they are - in a state of separation - but the majority of this race wish to fare once more into the world. The arrival of our trio may be the ballast that tips the scales in the favor of revolution!
name: Wrath of the Dragon Part 3

description: As Two-Face continues his rampage through Gotham City, more light is shed on his past. Who is Carrie Kelley and how can her mysterious connection to Harvey Dent help Batman?
name: The Big Burn: Sparks

description: A BATMAN: ZERO YEAR tie-in! There’s a dark force of nature that’s forming in Gotham City...A face laughing in the dark that will one day tear Jason Todd’s life apart. What are his plans for the Red Hood Gang? And who else will rise out of the shadows to guide Jason Todd one step closer to his destiny?
name: Zero Year: The Beckoning Dark

description:
A BATMAN: ZERO YEAR tie-in! Kate Kane is called home to attend a family funeral. But when an electrical storm creates havoc for the people of Gotham, an inexperienced Kate can’t deny her duty to protect the innocent!

Note: The solicit above is the revised version that was released after J.H. Williams III and Haden Blackman left the book over creative differences, prompting a new plot direction. Below is the original solicit for the cancelled story:

The no-holds-barred battle between Batwoman and Batman threatens to kill them both!
name: Zero Year: ...Or High Water

description:
Buddy Baker invades Hollywood to battle Brother Blood—and that’s before things get really weird!

The Cult of Brother Blood has taken over the Hollywood Screen Awards and are killing hostages until Animal Man shows up s that they may kill him instead. Animal Man, who is watching this all being broadcast is ready to give himself up to save the hostages but his wife Ellen talks him out of it and they agree to save everyone, together.

In the Red, Shepard and Socks lead Maxine to Mountains of Muscle, where she'll be safe from Brother Blood and the King of the Limbs, but just before they head into a safe cave it begins to rain blood. This act carries over into the real world where is starts raining blood in Hollywood. This gives Animal Man and Ellen, an even more sense of urgency, and once inside Animal Man takes on Brother Blood's cult head on, while Ellen sneaks around back stage.

Animal Man is able to subdue the leader, but before he can detain the others, they all commit suicide, so that there souls go to the Red to be aide to Brother Blood and the King of the Limbs. Then as Buddy finds Ellen, he is teleported to another world full of alien animals who start to attack him.
name: Hollywood Babylon, Part 2 of 2

description: Separated from their leader Captain Cold and trapped in Metropolis, the Rogues must fight for their lives against the Secret Society's secret weapon: the horrifying Parasite!
name: Shattered

description: After the stunning end of “Lights Out,” where is Kyle Rayner?! Or...WHEN is Kyle Rayner? And more important, WHY is Kyle Rayner? Answers to all these questions and more as the series rockets off to the outer limits of the DC Universe!
name: All Tomorrow's Parties

description: Following the shocking events of TRINITY WAR, Pandora can now physically harm the Seven Deadly Sins! But by going after Greed and Sloth at the same time, she may have bitten off more than she can chew. Plus: A surprising new player takes the stage, determined to end the immortal Pandora’s life!
name: End the Curse, Part 2: Great Legends

description: BLACK CANARY: ZERO YEAR?! Well, it’s definitely a BATMAN: ZERO YEAR tie-in issue as we look into a pivotal moment in Black Canary’s history! Don’t miss assassins, mystery men and an ancient evil in Gotham City!
name: Zero Year: Sunrise
